radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated at the base, measuring up to 12 mm with wall thickening and mucosal enhancement. Edema and stranding in the fat adjacent to the appendix. Mild wall enhancement and thickening of the adjacent terminal ileum. No acute abnormality in the visualized lung bases, heart base, liver, gallbladder, biliary tree, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys.
